TY  - JOUR
AU  - Hirshleifer, David
AU  - Mai, Dat
AU  - Pukthuanthong, Kuntara
T1  - War Discourse and Disaster Premium: 160 Years of Evidence from the Stock Market
PY  - 2025
Y1  - 2025/02/01
DO  - 10.1093/rfs/hhae081
JO  - The Review of Financial Studies
JA  - Rev Financ Stud
VL  - 38
IS  - 2
SP  - 457
EP  - 506
SN  - 0893-9454
AB  - Using a semisupervised topic model on 7 million New York Times articles spanning 160 years, we test whether topics of media discourse predict future stock market excess returns to test rational and behavioral hypotheses about market valuation of disaster risk. Media discourse data address the challenge of sample size even when disasters are rare. Our methodology avoids look-ahead bias and addresses semantic shifts. Our discourse topics positively predicts market excess returns, with War having an out-of-sample $R^{2}$ of 1.35%. We call this effect the war return premium. The war return premium has increased in more recent time periods.
Y2  - 2/8/2025
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1093/rfs/hhae081
ER  - 



